<h2 style="text-align: center"><span style="color: rgb(249, 115, 22)">üî• FINAL Fireside Chat Series this October! üî•</span></h2>

[Sign-up to attend on Thursday the 30th](https://the-turing-way-fireside-chats.start.page/) our session on <span style="color: rgb(35, 35, 35)"><strong>Good Governance Practices for the Long-Term Health of Open Initiatives</strong>. This session will feature speakers from Organizational Mycology and MetaDocencia.</span>

Please share on [Bluesky](https://bsky.app/profile/turingway.bsky.social/post/3lt2kymg6zk2w), [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7346495437069070338), [Twitter](https://x.com/turingway/status/1940729846667399317), and [Mastodon](https://fosstodon.org/@turingway/114788990373219266)

We look forward to seeing you there!

<img src="https://assets.buttondown.email/images/0b31a115-bcdf-4760-87bc-b3f77a5b6ade.png?w=960&amp;fit=max" width="618" draggable="false">

  
[*<u>The Turing Way Fireside Chat series</u>*](https://www.google.com/url?q=https://book.the-turing-way.org/community-handbook/fireside-chat.html&sa=D&source=calendar&usd=2&usg=AOvVaw09ggOaiuO9H6KVbjEfXM2j)¬†*features experts, champions and their projects from across different international communities in reproducibility, open research, ethics, collaboration and everything in between.*  
  
<span style="color: rgb(31, 31, 31)"><em>This series are&nbsp;</em></span>¬†***hosted in collaboration with the*** [***Software Sustainability Institute (SSI)***](https://www.software.ac.uk/) <span style="color: rgb(31, 31, 31)"><em>with a monthly edition from June through November 2025.</em></span>

You can also find the recording of our previous September session on **Governance frameworks, examples and resources from open source networks** in our [YouTube channel](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iPR2P2Jyj1U).

